        <updateDate>2025-06-04T10:12:05Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;This bill allows a state or local authority (e.g., a transit authority) to use public transportation grants to make a partial advance payment for bus rolling stock (e.g., transit buses).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Specifically, a public transportation grant recipient may use grant funds to make an advance payment of not more than 20% of the total purchase order value of a bus rolling stock vehicle without requiring the vehicle manufacturer to provide a performance bond (or&amp;nbsp;similar financial arrangement). In order to make an advance payment, the&amp;nbsp;recipient must meet certain requirements. For example, the recipient must have a signed purchase order and an executed contract with a vehicle manufacturer that includes advance payment provisions.&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>To establish limitations on advanced payments for bus rolling stock, and for other purposes.</title>
